HOW I MET NICK SERRANO —

I've told this story before, but when you're my age you're forgiven for repeating yourself!

During the worst days of the pandemic, I decided to rewatch the epic TV series "The Sopranos." Suddenly not having my nights packed with concerts meant I had a lot of time on my hands, and I'd often watch multiple episodes at a sitting, usually on my iPad, often in the bathtub while drinking a martini.

Simultaneously, I started seeing posts from the feed of my now buddy @nickvserrano. He was doing impressions of various characters from the series and he completely cracked me up. I dropped him a fan note, and he responded that he knew and liked my feed and was thinking about buying a leather jacket at the time. He wound up going with one from @schottnyc. Eventually we got together in person and immediately hit it off.

Originally from Connecticut and now living on Manhattan's Upper East Side, Nick is not only a very talented comedian. Among many other things, he's also an actor and writer with a day job as a marketing strategist. When you meet him one of the first things you notice--besides his impeccable hair-is his rich and resonant voice, so it wasn't a surprise to learn that he also does voiceovers. This guy has talent, charisma, and personality to burn.

Nick and I have hung around a fair amount lately, all to my benefit. He's such an incredibly thoughtful, caring, and generous person. Not to mention hilarious. Maybe it's because of some similar family dynamics that we have experienced, but we just clicked. The repeated feeling I have when we talk or text is,
"Wow, this guy just gets me."

I'm already dreaming of the evening when I'm in the audience and he wins an Emmy for one of his comedy specials. If he doesn't acknowledge me from the stage I will pelt him with a spitball. For now, I'm just incredibly grateful to know this beautiful dude. And, lucky for him, this @ironheartdenim chambray, which somehow shrank and is now too tight on me, is not too tight him on him. Some guys get all the breaks, but this is one dude who really deserves them.

I only have four hands 🪷 @fspalmbeach
